{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VxiJKybiwqaFXPxRpnLQCA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of the review:\n\n**Task reviewed:** theme-edit-delete-ui (Add edit and delete UI for theme owners)\n\n**Findings:** All acceptance criteria met. The UI correctly shows edit/delete controls only for owners, handles inline delete confirmation, edit mode for all fields (name, description, visibility, colors, fonts), live preview updates, and loading states.\n\n**Bugs fixed:**\n\n1. **Slug mismatch after rename (critical)** — The client-side `slugify()` used `replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, \"-\")` while the server's `generateSlug()` used `replace(/\\s+/g, \"-\").replace(/[^a-z0-9-]/g, \"\")`. Plus the server's `uniqueSlug()` might append `-2`, `-3` etc. for collisions. After renaming, the client would redirect to the wrong URL. Fixed by making `themes.update` return `{ slug }` and using that for the redirect.\n\n2. **Self-collision in `uniqueSlug` during update** — When updating a theme's name, `uniqueSlug()` would find the current theme's own slug as a collision. Fixed by adding an `excludeId` parameter to skip the current theme during uniqueness checks."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":133,"cache_read_input_tokens":52604,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":133},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ceec0539-6478-4eeb-897f-84ed3b4ac287","uuid":"93443122-b30a-45ff-b131-b20b8caeb402"}
